Good food, fast service
Excellent service. Food is good, priced right. Juice bar makes very healthy tastey drinks as well.
I tried this place once with my friend and I am obsessed ever since. I like the good ambience and tasty food and drinks. They never disappoint.

There are so many good options at this place. Avocado Chicken sandwich, Mediterranean Chicken Wrap. I just don’t believe they dont have many great reviews. Prices are quite low for Manhattan. My favorite place around 145. Guys and girls that work here are so hard working and nice people. 5 stars!
Yo the chicken & rib combo. The best I ever had i recommend this place to anybody.
A little pricey but well worth the price.   They make great sweet bananas

I absolutely love this restaurant and is one of my go to eats. They make many different foods such as their Rotisserie Chick 🐥, Ribs, salads BBQ 🐔 wings, Steaks,Tinga Bowl and Burrito Bowls which come with side orders range from corn, mash potatoes, salad, lemon wedges, french and sweet potato fries, potato salad. Also they make smoothies, hot and cold coffee, tea and soda. The people there are very friendly and you can use their app or call for delivery  which is free. Uber Eats, Seemless and Grubhub deliver as well but with fees.
Fantastic tasting food... their ribs and chicken is the boom.

Beware ordering during the pandemic! The Delivery Person was not wearing a mask and didn't follow instructions on the order to leave it in the lobby, or my verbal instructions when they called to be let in. When I called the restaurant to make it right they only offered to send me new food. Not sure how that helps the situation at all. The person is the health risk, not the food. They need to get their delivery team up to speed on standard safety protocols.

Food was not good at all. I got the ribs with mac and cheese and mashed sweet potatoes. The mac looked like Kraft but tasted even worse. The mashed sweet potatoes were bland and the ribs were hard and burnt, the sauce wasn't good either. I took 2 bites of each and threw the rest away. Would have been 1 bite but I decided to make sure. Would not recommend.
The make me wait a lot, of the supposed time
Changed their name and the quality of the ingredients in their salads. Went from great to average.  Before they gave a full pita bread now they give you a half.  Don't think they lowered the prices.

Food was okay. My ceaser wrap was good and filling. My boyfriend said he gave his grilled chicken 🐔 sandwich a 2 (Bread was soggy, etc). I enjoyed the wings as well as the cheesecake. A bit over priced for the food received.
Canteen grade rice and mashed potatoes. Dry tasteless overcooked grilled chicken. Salad is what earned the second star. Otherwise it would’ve been one star.
The Philly chicken wrap, The broiled chicken & chicken cesar salads are delicious.  The service is fast and the food is made fresh to order except for the sides. Pricey but worth it!

Delicious. I got the philly chicken cheesesteak. It was oily but oh so good. We also purchased the grilled chicken bowl, 1/4 ribs and the grilled bbq wings. It was ready in 10 minutes, steaming hot and enough for everyone to eat.

American food with Latino flavor!!! Grilled chicken is Always fresh and cooked on the spot when you order it. The seasoning is on the money and the prices are good. I go for the 10$ grilled chicken meal walk in special And the portion is great so I always get two meals out of it. Workers are nice.

I’ve ordered from this Chirping Chicken location several times, and too many times my order was delivered inexcusably late. I did not receive any updates whatsoever, and when I called the restaurant, I was met with an attitude and dry answers for checking my order status.

Ridiculous amount of time for delivery!! We ordered at 11:15 pm they closed the restaurant at 12am we didn’t even get our order. It’s always more than an hour waiting time for delivery. Worst service ever!!

We came to this place for a meeting. my friend recommended this place.  Well, it was very successful. The crew welcomed us with a smile and we had a great feeling. The food was just great. We loved this restaurant very much and we will definitely return to this restaurant. Warmly recommended.

Very disappointed with my grilled chicken burrito bowl. The chicken was raw  and hard and the pico del gallo was very old, tomatoes was old. And no guacamole, just a slice of avocado. I remember when they first open, that burrito was one of the best bowls I have ever tasted but they just down graded especially when you order to go out. The food is not fresh, I won't be going back for a long long time and if I do I'll stay and eat there because that's only time they do it fresh. Smh

Grilled chicken leg was good with pita bread, didn't like their coleslaw also ordered chicken gyro and they put some sauce like it was a little bit of mayo! What happen to the sauce?! Thats what makes the sandwich! Are all chirping chicken like this or just the one on 145th in Harlem? Maybe I'll go back and let them know and they will do better
So so tasty, Ribs and chicken are the best!
Excellent food. My son and his big appetite like this small place. There is a restroom and only 4 tables, but there is usually space to seat and eat.
Nice small place to get ur lunch and u can dine in or take out. Grill veggies very gud im not much of veggie eater. The whole sweetpotatoes are great.and turkey burger.
The food is over priced but it taste great the ribs the chicken and even the tbone steak.
Disgusting food and service
Its was great, they give larg amount of food too...
Bad food bad portions they serve stale meat and it's too salty!
Portions are small but the store is clean and food is tasty.

The quality was amazing. However the the food was overpriced. Had they had more competitive pricing, they would have received a 5 start review.  Let's talk about the food: Fresh, fresh, fresh and juicy. The chicken was perfectly cooked. I had two orders. The half chicken with rice and Mac and cheese which for my wife and I ordered the wings and fries (don't judge me). The rest of the sides were perfectly cooked and nothing was dried out.  Overall, I will order from them again.

The grill barbecue chicken is sooooo good. I like it well done and with sweet baked patatoes. The staff is helpful and friendly. Cashier cgave me once the last sweet patato she was savig for herself.sweet i appreciate it girl! It was a yummy meal and i m always game for deliver that is one of the best using postmates.
Great Place

Excellent food...... charboiled chicken was the best  by far. Little area for dining however, clean and orderlly. Chicken wings are fire! Fresh mix green salad. Will be back
chicken was dry and so was the fries......sucked
The chicken was old n dry,  oh my , the bread was old, cold ,n hard , noped
Delicious chicken, baked sweet patatoes, rice and bean, salads and ribs. I like coming here when i crave delicious barbecue chicken. Its tasty, clean and great price

After a long day of work, I stopped into this restaurant to get some dinner and waited for about 15 minutes for my order. There were a few police officers ahead of me and they left with bags of food. I went up to the counter to find out what was take them out what is so long and was told that all the food was done and that I had to change my order for a quarter chicken because there was no more left. Was all of the quarter chicken give it to the police officers who came in to place an order I suspect without paying for it. I’ll never know, but what I do know is that I never go to this restaurant again.
Great

10:00 and guess they haven’t remade ice tea all day, had mold in my drink !!!!! Mad mold at the bottom. I should’ve took a picture to add to this review. Disgusted. Girl said “oh that’s just the tea, that’s something in the tea” Me: what do y’all put in it ?! Girl : nothing, idk what that is .  I want to throw up. Not hard to make ice tea fresh everyday.
SALUTE Great Chicken

I've eaten here several times already, and I'll say I always clean the plate. Being that chicken is in the title I'll start there plenty of options and a lunch special makes this spot a definite go to. However I will say some of the other meals can get a little pricey, so start with the special which last all day.
Great food & service
This is one of the better locations. Pleasantly surprised by the awesome service. Always well staffed and food comes out fast. Also very clean, that's a plus.
Nice, polite staff. I recommend the arroz con pollo. Tastes like home cooked, full of flavor.
Food is good
Polite and good food!
Excellent food clean new shop and the chicken is great.

Out of all the times I've been to chirping chicken this is by far my worst experience , customer service sucks ,they have a  young short Mexican decent with dark black hair was more interested in her phone and coworkers then me , I was waiting forever to have my order taken then when I ask what sides are available  the girl sucks her teeth with the attitude pointing up for me to refer to menu as if I was asking to much of her to tell me the sides , this use to be my favorite location manager is usually very friendly and brings my food to me and knows my order without me asking but the one day I choose to a different side and make a change , chirping chicken changed too I won't be going back to this location ever again!
Pretty good customer service

Food was undercooked. I mean my chicken was pink on the inside and mushy. I tried with this place but the service and the food is horrible. I got the food home and was so disgusted by what I saw. Double thumbs down 👎👎

Service here is not good at all. Staff members are always chatting with each other. My order was wrong twice. I tried to give it a chance due to it being some what new but they get a thumbs down from me.
Chicken is the best
Nice and clean place. Love the food
The chicken is amazing, the fries are nice and crispy. The salads are great as well. Friendly staff!! I recommend 🙃😊

Food is what you expect from a chirping chicken. I have gotten the 1/4 chicken w/ a salad special twice. No complaints, standard  rotisserie chicken.  My complaint is that the only two times I have been in this establishment to pick up my order, I have witnessed subpar treatment from the young ladies taking orders towards customers during both visits. The first time, a gentleman complained about the price of a bottle of water to which the young lady replied "so". Today,  a gentleman complained about them servicing police officers that walked in after him before him. The young lady rolled her eyes, turned her head away from the customer as to dismiss his complaint, & and did not acknowledge his statement or offer an explanation of why he was skipped.  Staff needs to be trained to deal w customers in a better manner. I was treated fine both times but was very turned off by the treatment I saw others receive.

This place is the bomb. The food is amazingly flavory. It's really a Greek Diner in disguise but we will keep that on the wraps. Just try the spinach pie and the gyro platter. Best place to eat in Harlem!
Great food and awesome service. One of my favorite places to eat.
Food was amazing and delicious
Love this place the chicken rice and beans with a side salad feels like heaven thanks staff members you all deserve a raise.

First time at any Chirping Chicken location; decent prices. The chicken is very good. They made a mistake a dropped a chicken wing in with my chicken fingers, but I didn't mind. That was good also. LOL
Great

We love Chirping Chicken!!! I am so glad it has finally opened near me!  We used to go to 106 st/ Columbus ave but now we can just walk to 145 street.  The chicken is delicious, the staff is friendly and place is clean.  A great place for lunch, dinner or just a snack.  I was going to take a picture of the food but it was gone to quickly, maybe next time.
